sections.heading: fences; Warner's Patent; requirements
sections.text: Fence known as Warner's Patent shall be at least four and one-half feet in height, and consist of not less than five boards; such boards to be of a width of not less than five inches, and one inch thick.SourceLaws 1867 (Ter.), ยง 3, p. 18;R.S.1913, ยง 2495;C.S.192
